                            <comment id="17574483" author="tilman" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2022 04:10:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Effect can be observed with the scandinavian crossed out small &quot;o&quot;, in the TrueType font TT1 (ZPYENO+Helvetica). Code octal 0370 (dec 248) = &quot;oslash&quot;. The font itself has &quot;oslash&quot; at position 161 so it&apos;s unclear why it doesn&apos;t work, more investigation is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;update:&lt;br/&gt;
In PDFDebugger &lt;tt&gt;font.getPath(248)&lt;/tt&gt; returns an empty path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17574507" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2022 06:01:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve checked different versions and it is not a recent regression. It doesn&apos;t work in any 2.0.x or 3.0.x version. BUT it works in 1.8.15 &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17574513" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2022 06:14:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve observed the same but it is related to font TT2. TT1 doesn&apos;t contain &quot;oslash&quot;. Maybe you simply mixed them up &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17574530" author="tilman" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2022 06:36:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe we&apos;re both right. I looked at this one, in the first content stream. PDFDebugger doesn&apos;t show the glyph, but DTL does&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
